{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I'm Dr. David Hanson, and I build robots with character."},{"time":4000,"text":"And by that, I mean"},{"time":6000,"text":"that I develop robots that are characters,"},{"time":8000,"text":"but also robots that will eventually"},{"time":11000,"text":"come to empathize with you."},{"time":13000,"text":"So we're starting with a variety of technologies"},{"time":15000,"text":"that have converged into these conversational character robots"},{"time":19000,"text":"that can see faces, make eye contact with you,"},{"time":21000,"text":"make a full range of facial expressions, understand speech"},{"time":24000,"text":"and begin to model how you're feeling"},{"time":28000,"text":"and who you are, and build a relationship with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"I developed a series of technologies"},{"time":33000,"text":"that allowed the robots to make more realistic facial expressions"},{"time":36000,"text":"than previously achieved, on lower power,"},{"time":38000,"text":"which enabled the walking biped robots, the first androids."},{"time":42000,"text":"So, it's a full range of facial expressions"},{"time":44000,"text":"simulating all the major muscles in the human face,"},{"time":46000,"text":"running on very small batteries,"},{"time":48000,"text":"extremely lightweight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"The materials that allowed the battery-operated facial expressions"},{"time":53000,"text":"is a material that we call Frubber,"},{"time":55000,"text":"and it actually has three major innovations"},{"time":57000,"text":"in the material that allow this to happen."},{"time":59000,"text":"One is hierarchical pores,"},{"time":61000,"text":"and the other is a macro-molecular nanoscale porosity in the material."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65000,"text":"There he's starting to walk."},{"time":68000,"text":"This is at the Korean Advanced Institute of Science and Technology."},{"time":71000,"text":"I built the head. They built the body."},{"time":75000,"text":"So the goal here is to achieve sentience in machines,"},{"time":78000,"text":"and not just sentience, but empathy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"We're working with the Machine Perception Laboratory"},{"time":84000,"text":"at the U.C. San Diego."},{"time":86000,"text":"They have this really remarkable facial expression technology"},{"time":89000,"text":"that recognizes facial expressions,"},{"time":91000,"text":"what facial expressions you're making."},{"time":93000,"text":"It also recognizes where you're looking, your head orientation."},{"time":96000,"text":"We're emulating all the major facial expressions,"},{"time":98000,"text":"and then controlling it with the software"},{"time":100000,"text":"that we call the Character Engine."},{"time":102000,"text":"And here is a little bit of the technology that's involved in that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106000,"text":"In fact, right now -- plug it from here, and then plug it in here,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and now let's see if it gets my facial expressions."},{"time":117000,"text":"Okay. So I'm smiling."},{"time":122000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":124000,"text":"Now I'm frowning."},{"time":126000,"text":"And this is really heavily backlit."},{"time":130000,"text":"Okay, here we go."},{"time":132000,"text":"Oh, it's so sad."},{"time":134000,"text":"Okay, so you smile, frowning."},{"time":137000,"text":"So his perception of your emotional states"},{"time":139000,"text":"is very important for machines to effectively become empathetic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"Machines are becoming devastatingly capable"},{"time":146000,"text":"of things like killing. Right?"},{"time":150000,"text":"Those machines have no place for empathy."},{"time":152000,"text":"And there is billions of dollars being spent on that."},{"time":154000,"text":"Character robotics could plant the seed"},{"time":156000,"text":"for robots that actually have empathy."},{"time":158000,"text":"So, if they achieve human level intelligence"},{"time":160000,"text":"or, quite possibly, greater than human levels of intelligence,"},{"time":164000,"text":"this could be the seeds of hope for our future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"So, we've made 20 robots in the last eight years, during the course of getting my Ph.D."},{"time":171000,"text":"And then I started Hanson Robotics,"},{"time":173000,"text":"which has been developing these things for mass manufacturing."},{"time":177000,"text":"This is one of our robots"},{"time":179000,"text":"that we showed at Wired NextFest a couple of years ago."},{"time":181000,"text":"And it sees multiple people in a scene,"},{"time":184000,"text":"remembers where individual people are,"},{"time":186000,"text":"and looks from person to person, remembering people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"So, we're involving two things."},{"time":192000,"text":"One, the perception of people,"},{"time":194000,"text":"and two, the natural interface,"},{"time":198000,"text":"the natural form of the interface,"},{"time":200000,"text":"so that it's more intuitive for you to interact with the robot."},{"time":203000,"text":"You start to believe that it's alive and aware."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206000,"text":"So one of my favorite projects was bringing all this stuff together"},{"time":209000,"text":"in an artistic display of an android portrait"},{"time":212000,"text":"of science-fiction writer Philip K. Dick,"},{"time":214000,"text":"who wrote great works like, \"Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?\""},{"time":217000,"text":"which was the basis of the movie \"Bladerunner.\""},{"time":219000,"text":"In these stories, robots often think"},{"time":222000,"text":"that they're human, and they sort of come to life."},{"time":224000,"text":"So we put his writings, letters,"},{"time":227000,"text":"his interviews, correspondences,"},{"time":230000,"text":"into a huge database of thousands of pages,"},{"time":232000,"text":"and then used some natural language processing"},{"time":234000,"text":"to allow you to actually have a conversation with him."},{"time":236000,"text":"And it was kind of spooky, because he would say these things"},{"time":238000,"text":"that just sounded like they really understood you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"And this is one of the most exciting projects that we're developing,"},{"time":244000,"text":"which is a little character that's a spokesbot"},{"time":247000,"text":"for friendly artificial intelligence, friendly machine intelligence."},{"time":250000,"text":"And we're getting this mass-manufactured."},{"time":252000,"text":"We specked it out to actually be doable"},{"time":255000,"text":"with a very, very low-cost bill of materials,"},{"time":258000,"text":"so that it can become a childhood companion for kids."},{"time":262000,"text":"Interfacing with the Internet, it gets smarter over the years."},{"time":265000,"text":"As artificial intelligence evolves, so does his intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you so much. That's incredible."},{"time":270000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}